 HOW TO FIND THE DISTANCE OF A LINE SEGMENT BETWEEN TWO POINTS
Given 2 points in the coordinate plane, we can find the length of the line segment that connects them.
Step 1. Find the difference in x-coordinates between the two points.
    \begin{align*}
    x_2 - x_1 &= -4 - 1 = -5
    \end{align*} 
Step 2. Find the difference in y-coordinates between the two points.
    \begin{align*}
    y_2 - y_1 &= -10 - 2 = -12
    \end{align*} 
Step 3. Take the square root of the sum of the squares of those differences.
    \begin{align*}
    \sqrt{(-5)^2 + (-12)^2} &= \sqrt{25 + 144} \\
    &= \sqrt{169} = \boxed{13}
    \end{align*} 
### Now we know the length of the line segment.
Thus the length of the line segment is $\boxed{13}$ units.
